The paper presents a real-time robotic 3-D human tracking system, which involves computer vision, machine learning, and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The paper also involves computer vision techniques such as visual tracking and Gaussian Process Regression, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as the extended Kalman filter, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves the integration of multiple sensors, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
